This morning on @realmoney Irrational Exuberance? * The near universal faith in central bank liquidity's ability to buoy stocks may be unjustified in the face of weakening fundamentals * Time for another rant

I have recently made the case that the rise in financial asset prices has increasingly decoupled from the weakening fundamentals of the real economy and that the predictable spigot of central bank liquidity has encouraged excessive risk taking (and has contributed to too high

valuations), raising corporate incentives to overborrow and over engineer. Stated simply, the steady and relentless climb in stock prices has caused me to question how long and how far deteriorating fundamentals and historically high valuations can coexist. @jimcramer
